    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl4150403">
        <title>CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="6">
            <title>NOZZLE SLEEVE REPLACEMENT</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>REPLACE THE NOZZLE SLEEVE ONLY IF LEAKAGE IS PRESENT.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the nozzle sleeve puller adapter SE-2587A into the sleeve to be removed. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150425">4.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>This tool grips the nozzle sleeve by threading into it. Start the adapter into the nozzle
                            sleeve by striking it with a hammer. Then screw the nozzle sleeve puller adapter into the
                            sleeve using a wrench.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150423" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12034" filename="../figcg1/CG12034.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.23. Install Bottom Pressure Plate.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150424" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12036" filename="../figcg1/CG12036.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.24. Install Thermostat Opening Block-Off Plate.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150425" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11434" filename="../figcg1/CG11434.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.25. Install Nozzle Sleeve Puller Adapter into Sleeve.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect a slide hammer to the adapter and pull the sleeve from its bore. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150426">4.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the sleeve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the nozzle bore at the top and bottom using a rotary wire brush. Blow out with
                    filtered compressed air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite(r) 262 or equivalent to the nozzle sleeve contact points. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150427">4.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the nozzle sleeve using the nozzle sleeve installer
                    <emph type="bold">SE-2534</emph>. Drive the sleeve until it bottoms in the bore. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150428">4.28</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Nozzle sleeve installation can be done without removing the cylinder head except for the
                            #5 and 6 cylinders on "S" Series truck. Be sure to drain the coolant before replacing the
                            nozzle sleeves in chassis. When installing nozzle sleeves in chassis, piston should be
                            bottom dead center or installation tool may contact piston.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150426" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11435" filename="../figcg1/CG11435.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.26. Remove Nozzle Sleeve.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150427" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12037" filename="../figcg1/CG12037.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.27. Apply Loctite(r) to Nozzle Sleeve.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150428" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12038" filename="../figcg1/CG12038.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.28. Installing Nozzle Sleeve into Bore.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
